Neural Networks. 

Explanation: The paper discusses the application of the Gamma MLP, which is a type of neural network, to a speech phoneme recognition problem. The paper also compares the performance of the Gamma MLP to other neural network architectures, such as the TDNN and IIR MLP. The paper does not discuss any other sub-categories of AI such as Case Based, Genetic Algorithms, Probabilistic Methods, Reinforcement Learning, Rule Learning, or Theory.
